msgctxt "dn17:66.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, ānanda, rājā mahāsudassano subhaddaṃ deviṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When the queen had spoken, the king said to her:"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="50"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.193"></a>
msgctxt "dn17:67.1"
msgid ""
"‘Dīgharattaṃ kho maṃ tvaṃ, devi, iṭṭhehi kantehi piyehi manāpehi "
"samudācarittha;"
msgstr ""
"‘For a long time, my queen, you have spoken to me with loving, desirable, "
"pleasant, and agreeable words."

msgctxt "dn17:67.2"
msgid ""
"atha ca pana maṃ tvaṃ pacchime kāle aniṭṭhehi akantehi appiyehi amanāpehi "
"samudācarasī’ti."
msgstr ""
"And yet in my final hour, your words are undesirable, unpleasant, and "
"disagreeable!’"

msgctxt "dn17:67.3"
msgid "‘Kathaṃ carahi taṃ, deva, samudācarāmī’ti?"
msgstr "‘Then how exactly, sire, am I to speak to you?’"

msgctxt "dn17:67.4"
msgid "‘Evaṃ kho maṃ tvaṃ, devi, samudācara:"
msgstr "‘Like this, my queen:"

# Cp AN 6.16, where this advice is given by Nakulamata.
msgctxt "dn17:67.5"
msgid ""
"“sabbeheva, deva, piyehi manāpehi nānābhāvo vinābhāvo aññathābhāvo, mā kho "
"tvaṃ, deva, sāpekkho kālamakāsi, dukkhā sāpekkhassa kālaṅkiriyā, garahitā ca "
"sāpekkhassa kālaṅkiriyā."
msgstr ""
"‘Sire, we must be parted and separated from all we hold dear and beloved. "
"Don’t pass away with concerns. Such concern is suffering, and it’s "
"criticized."

msgctxt "dn17:67.6"
msgid "Imāni te, deva, caturāsīti nagarasahassāni kusāvatīrājadhānippamukhāni."
msgstr ""
